            h1 aWearable Application Example
                small <br><br>Festival
            <div id="about">
            <p> Some friends are going to a festival. They have previous experience of losing each other <br>in the crowds especially after concerts, and decide to create an aWearable application<br> to locate each other when needed.
            </p>
            <ul>
            <li> They start the aWerable toolkit web application, add each other as friends and set<br> privacy settings as prefered.</li>
            <li> They choose to use vibration and display  </li>
            <li> They set the vibration motor to vibrate when a friend is in- range and the display to show<br> distance and direction to this friend. When they feel the vibration they will know that a <br>friend is in range and that the display will show them where to look.</li>
            <li> Last they set the range, since the festival area is big they use a range of 200 meters.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><i> NB: Friends can create different applications and set different privacy settings.


            
            </div>
       






